# ============================================================================

print text "=========================================="
print text "Summary"
print text "=========================================="
print text ""
print text "Interrupt handling features demonstrated:"
print text "1. IDT initialization and management"
print text "2. Hardware interrupt handlers (timer, keyboard)"
print text "3. Exception handlers (page fault, GP fault)"
print text "4. Exception frame access and CPU state inspection"
print text "5. Error code decoding"
print text "6. Interrupt enable/disable (CLI/STI)"
print text "7. Handler registration and listing"
print text "8. IDT entry configuration"
print text "9. Handler cleanup"
print text ""
print text "Note: Actual interrupt delivery requires:"
print text "- Ring 0 (kernel mode) execution"
print text "- Hardware or software interrupt trigger"
print text "- Proper IDT configuration in CPU"
print text ""
print text "This example shows the NLPL API for interrupt handling."
print text "In a real OS, interrupts would fire automatically from hardware."
print text ""
print text "Examples complete"
